The '''Five Facet Mindfulness Questionnaire''' (FFMQ) is a psychological measurement to explore [[Mindfulness (psychology)|mindfulness]]. It is based on five independently developed mindfulness questionnaires that are bound together in a factor analytic study. The questionnaire consists of 39 items. The five facets are: observing, describing, acting with awareness, non-judging of inner experience, and non-reactivity to inner experience.

==Criticism==
The FFMQ has been criticised, with specifics including that negative and positive wording constituted substantive method effects.<ref>http://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/1073191112438743</ref>

